2.6.4 Removing Outliers using IQR¶

In [38]:
dataset_clean = dataset.copy()
In [39]:
dataset_numerical.columns
Out[39]:
Index(['age', 'policy_deductable', 'policy_annual_premium', 'umbrella_limit',

In [40]:
numerical_columns = list(dataset_numerical.columns)
q1 = dataset_clean[numerical_columns].quantile(0.25) # lower quartile
q3 = dataset_clean[numerical_columns].quantile(0.75) # upper quartile
iqr = q3 - q1 # interquartile range
lb = q1 - 1.5*iqr # lower booundary
hb = q3 + 1.5*iqr # higher boundary
for i in numerical_columns:
    dataset_clean = dataset_clean[(dataset_clean[i]>=lb[i]) & (dataset_clean[i]<=hb[i])]
